Preconditions:
- The input array `stones` is not null.
- The length of the input array `stones` is greater than or equal to 1.
- The length of the input array `stones` is less than or equal to 30.
- Each element in the input array `stones` is greater than or equal to 1.
- Each element in the input array `stones` is less than or equal to 100.
- The value of `k` is greater than or equal to 2.
- The value of `k` is less than or equal to 30.

Postconditions:
- The output is an integer representing the minimum cost to merge all piles of stones into one pile.
- If it is impossible to merge all piles of stones into one pile, the output is -1.